Description: Interior design, home staging and event planning firm.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Kim Perkins, Founder and CEO of the Candidly Kim Brand, focuses on timeless designs that can withstand new trends. Kim Perkins is passionate about design and creating unique, aesthetically appealing and functional spaces. A Caribbean born and Navy veteran, Kim always had a heart for serving others. She uses her exceptional skills in project management to take on multiple design portfolios with a focus on helping her clients turn their ordinary house into a dream home.   Kim had her first encounter with interior design when she retained a designer for services on her Gainesville VA townhome. She wanted to create an oasis in her home after a long day of work and commuting. After learning that her $5k budget would not suffice that designer’s plan, Kim took matters into her own hands and designed her first space in 2014 for under $3k. After successfully completing that, Kim decided that she wanted to help others achieve this same success in making their house into the home they desire and within their budget. “Getting your dream home has more to do with how you feel when you are in your home. If you don’t immediately feel the weight of the world disappearing from your shoulders then it’s not a home, it’s a temporary landing space.”   Kim has been able to help several Virginia residents achieve their interior design goals with the budget that they’ve set. “Most people think that you need to be a millionaire to hire an interior designer, that’s not true. A good interior designer can help you achieve the vibe that you are aiming for but it does require you to be flexible. You can’t expect a Restoration Hardware look with a Target budget. However, we can accomplish the vibe of luxury, if that’s what you’re aiming for”, says Kim.  Kim is a certified interior decorator and understands different design styles and types. She listens to the clients needs, learns about what matters to them most, takes into account their future goals with the home and recommends the best approach for design.
Industry Groups: Design, Events, Media and Entertainment, Real Estate

Description: Freedom2 is the developer of the Particle Encapsulation and Enhancement (P2E) Platform, which is designed to simplify tattoo removal.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Tattoos are all about self-expression and personal style; they're a way to showcase your unique point of view. And how many times have you changed your mind? Remember Angelina's ode to Billy Bob? We all know their love didn't last as long as the art commemorating it. Freedom2 was founded nearly ten years ago with the crazy idea that a permanent tattoo might be removable. Typical tattoo ink is made from insoluble pigments and remains in the skin forever. Laser treatments can be costly and painful, and ultimately might not even remove the tattoo completely. Thinking that there's got to be a better alternative, our founders began pursuing the idea that there could be a way to make tattoos that were permanent, and less expensive to remove. Full Description: TRIPLE SSS SPORTS CARDS - A TREASURE TROVE OF VINTAGE SPORTS CARDS Triple SSS Sports Cards, based in Shelby Township, Michigan, specializes in selling graded vintage collectible sports cards dated before 1975. The company is part of a solid and growing industry; a 2018 estimate put the size of the sports collectibles and memorabilia market in the United States at an annual $5.4 billion. Led by partners Mike and Mark Skerbe, Triple SSS Sports Cards works to provide knowledgeable, responsive, high-quality customer service to experienced and novice collectors alike. The company’s inventory includes baseball, football, basketball, and hockey cards, as well as non-sports cards. Recent inventory for sale on the company’s dedicated eBay page has included items such as 1955 Topps baseball card depicting Cleveland Indian catcher Jim Hegan, a 1961 Topps football card featuring Cleveland Browns running back Jim Brown, and a 1969 Topps card honoring Mike Cuellar, the Baltimore Orioles pitcher and Cy Young Award winner remembered as a four-time 20-game winner for the team. A regular at the National Sports Collectors Convention card show for over 25 years, Triple SSS is always interested in purchasing cards from potential sellers. Collectors with cards they’d like to discuss selling can contact the company at TripleSSSInc.com.
